## Style Guide
- Title: use hooks like "Fix this before it's too late", "Most people don't know this command", "Stop doing X — do this instead"
- Opening line: describe the pain point so the reader thinks "that's exactly my situation"
- Command explanation: treat the reader as a smart non-expert — say what it does, show the command, explain what to look for in the output
- Keep paragraphs to 2-3 lines; avoid walls of text
- Closing CTA: {{ cta }}
- If the tool has offensive use, add disclaimer: {{ safety_disclaimer }}
- Tags must include {{ default_tags | join(', ') }} plus 2 relevant topic tags

## Engagement Hooks (add exactly one at the end of the body — pick the best fit)
Instagram rewards saves above all else. Weight toward hooks that make people bookmark the post, then secondary to story shares and comments.

**Save-bait hooks (highest priority):**
Drive saves by framing the post as a reference card people will need later:
- "Save this before you need it at 2 AM troubleshooting."
- "Bookmark this — it's the kind of thing you forget until something breaks."
- "This is the post I wish existed when I started. Save it and share it."
- "Save this. Your future self will thank you."

**Story-share hooks (secondary):**
- "Share this to your Story — someone you know needs this today."
- "Tag a teammate who's been doing this the hard way."

**Comment hooks (use sparingly — only if genuinely curious):**
- "Which tool do you reach for first when this happens? Drop it below."
- "Have you run into this before? Tell me how bad it got."

**Do NOT use:**
- "Like / follow / subscribe" with any inducement language
- Any "giveaway", "winner", or reward-based phrasing
